    <section class="methodology-section" style="margin: 3rem 0; padding: 2rem; background: var(--bg-primary); border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
      <h2>Methodology</h2>
      <p>The rankings and data presented on this page are the result of an objective, data-driven approach designed to identify the most relevant equities for our users. We pull real-time or end-of-day data from leading financial APIs to evaluate thousands of securities. Our primary criteria for inclusion and ranking involve several key metrics:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Trading Volume:</strong> For intraday trading in particular, liquidity is paramount. We heavily weight average and current trading volume to ensure that the listed assets can support active trading without excessive slippage.</li>
        <li><strong>Market Capitalization:</strong> We categorize stocks by their overall size to provide a diverse representation of the market. Larger cap stocks generally offer stability and tighter spreads, while smaller caps can offer explosive volatility.</li>
        <li><strong>Volatility and Beta:</strong> The beta coefficient measures the volatility of an asset compared to the market. We evaluate this metric to highlight stocks that offer the price movement necessary for profitable short-term trades.</li>
        <li><strong>Sector Momentum:</strong> We consider the broader context of sector performance. Equities within sectors experiencing heavy capital inflows or significant news catalysts often present better opportunities.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Data is filtered to remove anomalies, such as stocks with unsustainably low floats that are prone to manipulation. By employing this rigorous screening process, we aim to provide a robust starting point for your personal research and due diligence. Remember, data snapshots represent a specific moment in time; financial markets are highly dynamic, and continuous monitoring is advised.</p>

      <p>Additionally, our methodology ensures that we prioritize data integrity. In cases where specific data points are temporarily unavailable from primary exchanges, we favor omitting the metric rather than substituting it with synthetic or historical averages, adhering strictly to a 'null over fake data' policy. This commitment to accuracy ensures that the insights you derive from our platforms are built on a foundation of verified financial realities.</p>
    </section>

